    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Job Deactivator\n\nRuns every 3 days and checks all active job listings. Any with a dead URL gets marked `inactive` in both Supabase and Google Sheet.\n\n📄 [Google Sheet](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Fazi5DwKujtGK22atp9c1EWhOxOFk82Mz39ErIkngpc)\n--- \n\n## 📽️[Workflow Walkthorugh](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1AQXt4d5utO9yWXKi8IwwZOAM71n9mT2g/view?usp=sharing)\n\n---\n##  Companion to Job Scraper — must use the same Supabase `jobs` table and Google Sheet.\n\n\n## How It Works\n1. Fetches all `status = active` jobs from Supabase\n2. Skips any with missing/invalid URLs\n3. Sends a HEAD request (batch of 5) to each `apply_url`\n4. Flags job as dead if:\n   - `404` or `410` response\n   - DNS failure or connection refused\n   - Redirect to `/jobs`, `/careers`, or `/` (soft-404)\n5. Updates `status = inactive` in Supabase + Google Sheet\n\nTransient errors (timeouts etc.) are ignored — job stays active.\n\n\n## Setup\n1. Import workflow into n8n\n2. Connect same **Supabase (Postgres)** + **Google Sheets** credentials as Job Scraper\n3. Activate\n\n\n## Customise\n- **Check frequency** → edit Every 3 Days trigger node\n- **Add more soft-404 patterns** → edit the `Find Dead Jobs` node (look for `SOFT_404_REDIRECT` block)",
        "height": 944,
        "width": 832
      },
